TextChange: Mother nature doesn't create perfectly symmetrical, smooth and always perfect leaves on trees, but that doesn't take away from the beauty.  I would love to see our society make a move from form to substance.  It's not what something looks like that determines it's value.  In fact, it's our very imperfections that make us perfectly unique to this world.\n
